That's exactly it. Samsung devices report `(hover: hover)` because of S-Pen support, even if you don't have one or aren't using it. So the current check fails:

```typescript
const isTouchDevice =
    typeof window !== "undefined" && window.matchMedia("(hover: none)").matches;
// → false on Samsung, because Samsung reports hover capability
```

The fix is to use `(pointer: coarse)` instead — it checks whether the primary input is a finger (low accuracy), which is `true` on all phones including Samsung:

